    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-10-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="305"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d305">
                <head>305. Memorandum From the <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    to the Assistant Secretary of State for Near Eastern, South Asian, and African
                    Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_RWM1" type="to">Rountree</persName>)<note n="1"
                        type="source" xml:id="d305fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files,
                        784A.56/10–656. Top Secret. a marginal notation on the source text reads:
                        “Mr. <persName corresp="#p_RWM1">Rountree</persName> saw.”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-10-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 6, 1956</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>General <persName corresp="#p_CLGCP1">Cabell</persName> advised me this afternoon
                    that a re-evaluation has been made by <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> and
                    the Air Force of all available information concerning the number of Mystere Mark
                    IV’s in Israel. It is the combined intelligence estimate, which they consider to
                    be reliable, <pb facs="0694" n="654" xml:id="pg_654"/> that there are in fact 60
                    Mark IV’s now in Israel. The Israelis do not have any Mark II’s and have
                    expressed the opinion that they do not wish any in view of the difficulties of
                    maintaining two different types.</p>
                <p>At my request, General <persName corresp="#p_CLGCP1">Cabell</persName> is going
                    to forward this information to the Secretary in New York through his own
                    communications system.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">
                            <hi rend="strong">H.H. Jr.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
